<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Toil3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Toil,</orth> vb. 1) intr. to labour, to exert one's strength, to make efforts: <bibl n="shak. son 25.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 25, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.28.8" default="NO" valid="yes">28, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 191</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.3" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.62" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.178" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 178</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 77</bibl>.<lb />2) trans. a) to put to pains and labour, to strain: <cit><quote>have --ed their memories,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>t. his wits,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.83" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 83</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>why this watch . . . so nightly --s the subject,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 72</bibl></cit>.
<lb />b) to weary, to fatigue: <cit><quote>--ed with works of war,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.96" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 96</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>